      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A solid red internet light on your router usually indicates a failed connection with your modem or ISP. First, check that the Ethernet cable is securely plugged into both the router's WAN port and your wall outlet or modem. If the cable looks fine, try power cycling both devices by unplugging them, waiting 30 seconds, and plugging them back in. If the issue persists, you may need to contact your internet service provider to check for outages or account problems.",
