      "role": "user",
      "content": "i already tried unplugging it and everything but the light is still red. i checked the cables too and they seem fine. is there anything else i can try before i have to call the company? maybe some kind of reset button or something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, you can try a factory reset by pressing and holding the small recessed reset button on the back of the router for about 10-15 seconds until all lights flash. **Note:** This will erase your saved Wi-Fi passwords and router settings, so you will likely need to reconfigure your network afterward. If that doesn't work, verify if your ISP has scheduled maintenance or check their status page online, as server-side issues are common.",
