    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "does the reset button usually fix it or is it more of a last resort? i'm kinda worried about losing all my settings but i really need the internet back for work. is there any way to tell if the actual signal coming into the house is broken vs just the router itself?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A reset is often a last resort because it wipes your custom Wi-Fi name and passwords, forcing you to set them up again from scratch. If you are worried about losing settings, check if the red light persists on your modem (the box that connects to the wall) as well; if the modem is showing a problem too, the issue is likely with your internet service rather than the router. You can also try connecting directly to your modem using an Ethernet cable to see if the signal itself is working without your router in between.",
      "source": "target",
